name: Ferry lane
description: Good views by the river but overlooked by the house opposite.

name: A483 Car Park
description: Car park off the A483. Free to park and a nice quiet spot with pleasant surroundings.

name: Pembrey, Penybedd Road
description: Small car park with close to forest walks. Some benches close but no facilities.

name: Cwmgiedd Forestry Commission Car Park
description: Secluded car park with no barriers. Peaceful spot in the woods next to the river. Easy access to forest walks.

name: National Trust Car Park near Coelbren
description: Quiet car park near Henrhyd Waterfall. Manoeuvring can be tough in you're in a big vehicle or the car park is busy, it does get busy on weekends. Really easy access to Waterfall walks.

name: Penrallt y Gardde, Picnic Spot
description: Small picnic area with tables. small track off road

name: Kidwelly Long Stay
description: Free car park with no restrictions. Toilets and shops close by. Poor signal

name: Mountain Road, Brynamman
description:
Awesome. 

Layby with amazing views. Warden has seen me and not said anything, stayed there several times.

name: Melincourt Waterfall
description: No restrictions as far as I know. Access to the waterfall walk.

name: Raven Trail Head
description: Trail head for the Black Raven trail at Brechfa. Some porta-loos that aren't too bad normally. Gets busy on weekends with riders but quiet in evenings. Short drive into Brechfa where there are some good pubs.

name: Pont ar Daf
description: Main car park for the Pen y Fan walk. Fairly large but gets extremely busy and fills up on weekends in good weather (check the satellite image). Free to park and no restrictions with a public toilet.

name: River Tawe
description: Stayed here multiple times, police checked up at 2am once and told me to keep my ears open - it can be a bit sketchy but generally fine. Don't take the piss as there used to be height restrictions here to stop campers / lorries.

name: Cwm Rhaeadr
description: Bottom of the Cwm Rhaeadr mtb trail and waterfall walk. Gets busy on weekends but great for overnight camping.

name: Llwyn-on Reservoir
description: Small free car park on the edge of the reservoir. Nice and quiet with great views of the scenery.

name: Llandysul Paddlers
description: Car park for Llandysul Paddlers Canoe Club, they're fine with camping for a couple of nights especially if you're paddling. Pub is just down the road and waffle factory provides amazing smells!

name: Penrice, Gower
description: Quiet spot, Internet's not the best but with an antenna it's ok. Hunts on the weekends meet here, can get pretty hectic, stayed there all day and no complaints. It's silent at night apart from the wildlife.

name: Penclawdd
description: Beautiful spot and quiet. Good Internet... watch out for high tides! Got woken up by a bus driver at 7am with my wheels under water and the tide still coming in, I left pretty sharpish but it didn't really come in any more.

name: Cefn Bryn, Gower
description: Good place to stay, usually some other campers there too... watch out for cows using your van as a scratching post.

name: Lay-by near Llangrannog
description: Quiet lay by up the hill. MWB and SWB only as turning up the hill is a touch tight...

name: Bryn Bettws
description: Free spot part way around "The Wall" trail. Road can be a bit rough getting up there but its a great spot.

name: Afan Forest Park Visitor Centre
description: Lots of parking at the trail head for Y Wal, Blue Scar and Penhydd. Parking is around £5 for 24 hours.

name: Glyncorrwg Visitor Centre
description: Car Park at the trail head for Whites Level, Blade and W2. Parking may be £5 for over night. Lots of space.

name: Quiet Lane on North Gower
description: Good views and a bit of space at the end of a lane on North Gower overlooking the Loughor Estuary

name: Usk Reservoir Parking
description: Parking for the Usk Reservoir,  quiet and out of the way with great views.

name: Bridleway off Heol Senni
description: A bit tricky to get to off the main road but the spot is flat and the views are amazing.

name: Cray Reservoir Lab-by 1
description: Quiet Lay-by near Cray Reservoir off the A4067

name: Cray Reservoir Lay-by 2
description: Quiet Lay-by near Cray Reservoir off the A4067

name: Willow Springs Campsite
description: Pretty campsite just outside of Afan Forest Park. Good signal and the campsite has wifi. Dog Friendly, great facilities and friendly owner.

name: Rhigos Viewpoint
description: Viewpoint over the Rhigos. Icecream van parks here on Summer days.

name: Resolven Car Park
description: Next to the river nice spot but next to the main road so occasionally a bit noisy at night.

name: Usk Reservoir Boat Launch
description: Parking next to the Usk Reservoir. Used for boat launches, fine for overnight.

name: Abergorlech Trail Head
description: Great spot for over night, gets busy on weekends with riders. Easy access to forest walks and mtb trails.

name: A470 Car Park near Pen y Fan
description: Large lay-by off the A470 just north of the main Pen y Fan car park. Fairly quiet at night and a great spot for star gazing.

name: Burry Port, Factory Road
description: Within ear shot of the beach, other lay-bys on the road down to the spot at the end. If car park is busy it can be challenging to manoeuvre.

name: Castell Henllys
description: Rural parking in an Iron Age village close to a small chapel.

name: South of Dolgellau, Lay-By
description: Exposed site, great views. Occasionally quite noisy as its on the Mach Loop.

name: Manorbier Beach Car Park - 2
description: Great views from the car park just off the side of the road, slightly sloping but not too bad.

name: Trywenyn Top
description: Great spot for paddlers - top car park for Canalfon Tryweryn Center.

name: Llanion Cove
description: Large parking at the mouth of Cosheston Pill. Great views of the estuary, quiet but no services.

name: Nelson Quay
description: Large gravel car park next to the Milford Haven Marina. Free to park, shops and restaurants in easy walking distance.

name: St Annes Head
description: Car park in the middle of nowhere, amazing views. Signs say no overnight parking but no issues reported.

name: Dale Beach
description: Large gravel car park with no regs. Occasionally gets busy so be sensible and considerate.

name: Swanage
description: Council car park, signs say no sleeping but its not enforced and regularly used for overnighting. Toilets short walk away on the harbour

name: Portland Lighthouse
description: Large parking that's attached to the lighthouse. Empty in the evening, overnight sleeping is prohibited but not enforced.

name: Portland Cliff Top
description: Amazing Views. Park right on top of the cliff with views over the sea. Says no over night parking but as with many spots in the area doesn't seem to be enforced. Well used by climbers as easy access to crags - check UKC.

name: Aberiddy Beach
description: Gets busy on sunny summer days. No issues when staying here. Toilers but might not always be open. Gorgeous spot with great access to Blue Lagoon for cliff jumping!

name: Newgale Beach
description: Sometimes there is a small charge. Toilets are open most of the time. Right on the beach. Park back from the beach in windy weather as wind can pick up stones

name: Saint Dogmaels Lay By
description:
Small lay by, with great views, a few benches and a bin. 
Unrestricted between 6pm and 8am, then 4 hours free, only applies April through September.
Close to pub with good food.

name: Swansea Marina Coastal Car Park
description: No complaints when staying here. Good views and easy access into town.

name: Ogmore Riverside
description: Lovely view of the estuary and castle. Thatched roof houses near surround.

name: Moelgrove
description: Lay-by right on the coast. Normally only used by walkers and coasteering groups.

name: Wisemans Bridge
description: Car park is right on the beach, only a short walk from a pub and a public toilet not far away. Not had any issues when staying here.

name: Ffestiniog, Upper Cynfal Gorge
description: Car park in the middle of nowhere. Incredible view, can get windy.

name: Lake side, Tryweyn
description: Lake side glamping. Toilets, fire pit, views. Just watch out for the people who occasionally escape from the care home just down the road.

name: Llyn Aled Reservoir
description: Small spot off the side of the road. Quiet and out of the way with great views of the dam. Can get quite windy.

name: Afon Llugwy Forestry Falls
description: Nice quiet spot in the middle of nowhere.

name: The Gooseberry Bush
description:
Overnight parking allowed, alcohol served till midnight and breakfast from 8.
But it is a Weatherspoons car park

name: Lay-by near Scout Hut
description: Quiet-ish lay-by outside Scout Hut and residential property.

name: Car Park near Manorbier YHA
description: Great views at a secluded car park near YHA, over the cattle grid, follow the road to the end. Small ‘no camping signs’ but no issues reported.

name: Manorbier Bar
description: Great views overlooking Manorbier Bay. Small lay-by, with signs saying no overnight parking but no issues reported.

name: Pembroke Main Street
description: Car Park opposite Tourist Information office. Sign posted no sleeping in vehicles but apparently not enforced. £1.50 for all day till 7pm.

name: Pembroke Dock, Front Street Street Parking
description: Parking on a quiet street, right on the sea front. Pub at the end of the street. Close to the ferry terminal.

name: Jetty Beach Lay-by
description: Occasionally busy spot with great views.

name: Westdale Bay Lay-by
description: Small lay by at the top of the path down to Westdale Bay. Quiet spot with beautiful views. Level lay-by. Toilet and bins in Dale just down the road.

name: Abbotsbury Parking
description: £3.50 for 24hrs or £2 after 4pm. Fairly level hardstanding. Close to the village which is pretty and friendly. Lots of tea rooms and a couple of pubs. Beach is just over a mile walk away. Good place to stop.

name: Bridport Parking
description: Parking with great view of the sea

name: Grass Car Park
description: Grassy area close to public toilet and church right on the coastal path.

name: Mawddach
description: Small car park next to some toilets an a river.

name: Lochwinnoh
description: Good reception, park on the wooded side of the car park, quite a busy place but no issues.

name: Rosewall Campsite
description: Large campsite with great views. No caravans, but vans are fine. About £15 a night.

name: Porth Nanven
description: Picturesque cove with enough parking space for about 8 vehicles. Lots of walking options, no amenities but quiet quiet. Access is though a narrow windy lane.

name: Embankment Rd Free Car Park
description: Free car park, easy walk to the town center. Close to grassy play area, beach and public toilets. Can get busy during the day but was quiet at night.

name: Carn Brea
description: Flat spacious car park near Lands End. No facilities. Owned by the National Trust but not pay and display, there is an honesty box for donations.

name: Yr Eifl
description: Amazing spot with great views. Totally silent at night. Flat hard standing. Pub and cafe are down the hill in the village. Beach at the bottom of the valley is pristine.

name: Llyn Trawsfynydd
description: Free car park with lots of space. Short walk to a great cafe. Access to woodland walks and you can fish in the lake. Just off the access road for a permanently closed nuclear power station.

name: South Stack
description: Access to South Stack and lots of sea cliff climbing. Medium gravel car park. Quiet but exposed. Just past RSPB gift shop and cafe - opens at 10am.

name: Trearddur Bay
description: Large beach car park, close to cafe and shops. Parking is free from 8pm. Height limited to 2.1m

name: Tyn y Mynydd
description: Car park in Mynydd Bodafon. Quiet spot with access to lots of walks.

name: Cefni Reservoir
description: Free car park with no restrictions. Spot is in the woods next to the lake. Short walk to some beautiful tranquil locations.

name: Capel Curig
description: Free parking close to the shops of Capel Curig. Toilets are just down the road. Sunsets are great here.

name: Dinas Mawddwy
description: Quiet car park with play area close to the pub and post office.

name: Machynlleth
description: Car park in the centre of Machynlleth. £3.20 for all day, free after 6pm, camping is allowed 1 night in 7.

name: Nolton Haven
description: No view but convenient parking in the centre of Nolton Haven. Really close to the beach.

name: Garn Fawr Fort
description: Gravel car park with great views out to the coast. Short walk up to the top of the Iron Age Fort for panoramic views. Very quiet.

name: Strumble Head Lighthouse
description: Car park at the Strumble Head Light house. No restrictions, can be a bit exposed. Incredible views.

name: Goodwick
description: Large car park in Goodwick, close to the beach and local amenities.

name: New Ground Road
description: Several parking spots along the New Ground Road. Notice says no overnight parking but normally isn't enforced.

name: Strumble Head
description: Just up the road from another spot. No restrictions, amazing views, can get windy.

name: B3351 Lay-by
description: Quiet lay-by with no signs. Views over Bournemouth and Brownsea Island.

name: The Warren
description: Gravel car park next to the beach. Surrounded by trees. Narrow access lane, can get busy so park respectively. Beach cafe is about 20 minutes walk down the beach.

name: Car Park on the Afon Gain
description: Incredible isolated spot. As beautiful as many of the spots in the area. Fantastic scenery and outstanding walks. The Afon Gain has rapids and a waterfall minutes away. Extremely limited signal, and no facilities. Great spot for road cycling! Properly in the wilderness, respect the area and leave it better than you found it.

name: B4407 Car Park
description: Amazing spot next to small lake. Totally secluded. Beautiful location but can get windy. No phone signal.

name: Llyn Peris Lay-by
description: Large lay-by off the side of the road at the bottom of Llyn Peris. Great views and pretty quiet at night. Easy walk to the pub.

name: Porth Cwyfan Lay-By
description: Lay-by lover looking the beach and Celtic Church in the sea. Beautify spot. End of a narrow track.

name: Llynnau Mymbyr Lay-by
description: Lay-by on Llynnau Mymbyr. Lake is great for swimming and washing. Sometimes a bit windy but stunning views.

name: Fork in the Road
description: The road splits and there is a flat spot perfect for overnight. Really quiet and next to a small steam. This spot is the original background image for Van Spots!

name: A4086 Lay-by
description: Large pubic lay-by that's set back from the road. Flat with good views. Quiet and discreet.

name: Liyn Cwm Bychan
description: Great area close to the lake and next to a stream. Access road is quite narrow. Large area with lots of flat spaces. Cost is £5 for overnight via a honesty box.

name: Harlech
description: Car park in town. Nice and quiet at night. Walking distance of castle and beach.

name: Mawddach Lay-by
description: Large lay-by about 5 miles outside of Barmouth. Quiet and setback quite a long way from the road.

name: Penmaenpoll Toll Bridge
description: Car park just off the toll bridge road. Restaurant and hotel nearby. Public toilets are left unlocked. Signs say no tent camping. Bridge closes at 6.30pm. Honesty box for parking.

name: Porth Ysgaden
description: Stunning location. Quiet at night but car park is used frequently during the day by walkers. No restrictions.

name: A30 Lay By
description: Sheltered lay-by on the A30. Surrounded by trees

name: Overgrown Car Park
description: Small area off Lake Vyrnwy. Partially overgrown.

name: Sennen Cove
description: Toilets open all night but they're not the best. £4.00 overnight until 9am. Height limit 2.3m. Often gets busy because of the great location.

name: Trethewey
description: Small parking area at a picnic spot. Great for over night but no amenities.

name: Foel Friog
description: Forestry Commission Car Park at the entrance to the village of Aberllefenni. Picnic benches on the bank of the river. Cute place with no restrictions. Lots of walks in the area. Good signal.

name: Lake Vyrnwy Picnic Area
description: Stunning location on lake Vyrnwy. Overnight parking is prohibited but sometimes you can get away with it. Cafe and canoe rental are close.

name: Lake Vyrnwy Lay-by
description: Small parking area on the lake. Overnight parking prohibited but can sometimes get away with it. Stunning location.

name: Rhiwargor Waterfall
description: No view of the lake but close to lots of great walks. Quiet spot next to picnic benches.

name: Climachx Trail
description: Parking for the Cimach-X trail. Approach to car park is steep and can be inaccessible in winter

name: Bwlch Nant yr Arian
description: Pay and display car park at the forest visitor centre.

name: Caerfai Bay Cliff Top
description: Small sized car park overlooking Caerfai bay and St Brides Bay. Never had any problems when staying here over night. Great access to the costal path and climbing spots around St Davids.

name: Porth Neigwl
description: Hell's Mouth car park. Free parking spot with great views of the mountains. Short walk to the beach, great for surfing. Few bins but no other facilities. No restrictions.

name: Traeth Penllech
description: Quiet car park with access to the beach and the coastal path.

name: Roadford Lake
description: Large car park and picnic area. Great views over the lake. Nice and out of the way, peaceful.

name: Chevron Fold
description: Quiet cliff top lay-by. Stunning views.

name: Black Rock Cafe
description: £15 for overnight parking. Water and black bins available but no other facilities. Amazing views over Widemouth Bay.

name: Widemouth Beach
description: Council car park on the beach. Toilets and outside shower. Free after 5pm, paid during the day. Not normally an issue with staying over night.

name: Crooklets Beach
description: £5 for overnight parking. Parking pass from Rosie's Cafe.

name: Coombe Beach
description: National Trust car park. Payment is optional. Access is a bit narrow.

name: The Jamaica Inn
description: £10 per night to stay in the Jamaica Inn car park. Easy access off the A30. Inn has lots of history and is apparently quite haunted.

name: Illand
description: Quiet lay-by off the road in Illand. No restrictions. No services. Short drive to the Racehorse gastro pub.

name: Rowtor
description: Gravel car park at the base of Row Tor. No through road so quiet. Views are amazing right in the middle of the moors.

name: Prewley Moor
description: Good for overnighting, just on Dartmoor. Direct access to National Cycle Route 27. There's also bike hire available in walking distance from the spot. No services at spot, but campsite, pub and service station are also walking distance. About a mile to Stourton Tor for some great views.

name: Broad Park
description: Small campsite, £16 per night. Nice a quiet, good facilities. Good access further into Devon and Cornwall.

name: Riverbank Long Stay
description: Car Park on the River Torridge, toilet facilities. £5 overnight parking. £3 during the day.

name: Westward Ho!
description: Main car park in Westward Ho! Short walk to beach and close to amenities. No services but overnight parking is allowed at £5 per space.

name: Appledore
description: Large council car park. £5 for overnight, max stay 2 nights. Overlooking the river. Public toilets are available.

name: Instow Sea Front
description: Limited number of free parking spots. Next to a dog friendly beach and cafes and restaurants.

name: Taw Estuary
description: Lay by next to an estuary. Nice quiet spot. Bike shop and hire just down the road on Fremington Quay.

name: Croyde Car Park
description: Parking at the top of the hill. Some signs about overnighting but its been okay in the past. Car park does sometimes get busy.

name: Wollacombe Esplande
description: Lots of parking. Popular spot with surfers. Signs say no overnight parking, but not enforced and local don't mind as long as your considerate.

name: Lee Beach
description: Long gravel car park right on the front. No restrictions. Nice and tranquil.

name: Hidden Valley Touring and Camping Park
description: Quiet and clean campsite. £12 per night.

name: Hele Bay
description: Small picnic area with great sea views. 5 mins from Illfracombe.

name: Treverven Camping
description: Quiet place close to the cliffs. Loads of amenities, including kitchen, washing machine, toilets, showers and a small shop.  About £27 a night.

name: Ros Vale
description: £6 per night. Some amenities.

name: Cregennan Lakes
description: Amazing spot next to Llynnau Cregennen. Great for swimming. Access road is steep and very night, large vans are unlikely to be able to make it up. Stunning Views. Recently signposted to saying no overnight parking but not enforced.

name: Rough Tor
description: 2 miles of singletrack to get to the bottom of Rough Tor. Close to a stream and totally remote

name: Disused Aerodrome near Crowdy Reservoir
description: Best to park on the western side in sight of the lake as model flyers and microlights sometimes use the strip. Good food at the Rising Sun pub.  Beautiful surrounded by nature. Hard standing on the disused runways. On Bodmin Moor so surrounded by sheep and grass with the reservoir close by. Easy access - pull off the road on any hardstand either in the open or in the shade of pine trees. There are sheep and wild ponies. Woodland walk popular with dog walkers.

name: The New Inn, Church Knowle
description: Landlord allows overnight parking for free. Double check in the pub to be sure. Pub opens at 1800.

name: Shore Road, Swanage
description: Parking on the seafront in Swanage. Signposted cars only so best to arrive late and leave early. 50p overnight parking cost. Close to nudist beaches.

name: The Tank Museum Parking
description: Parking of the Tank Museum

name: Affpuddle Car Park
description: Large car park just off the road. Width limited entry is the only limitation. Superb spot, surrounded by trees.

name: White Mill, Sturminster Marshall
description: Medium area enclosed by trees next to the River Stour. Nice and peaceful. 15 minute walk to the pub.

name: Blandford Road - Dog Walker Car Park
description: Nice free spot next to the main road. Quiet until dog walkers turn up in the morning.

name: B3081 Viewpoint
description: Lay-by on the B3081. Stunning views and the road isn't too busy.

name: Lime Kiln
description: Loads of space in parking areas nearby. Have been informed that there is a two-night policy by rangers. Toilets and the rangers office. Some stunning views and lots of walks.

name: Cartgate Lodge Cafe
description: Picnic spot but okay for overnight. Cafe was open to 10pm and there's a tourist information center.

name: Creech St Michael, Canalside Car Park
description: Nice quiet spot next to the canal. Shop and pub nearby. Surrounded by trees.

name: Lambert's Castle
description: Good quiet, shady spot off B3165.

name: Stonebarrow National Trust Car park
description: National Trust car park close to toilets and shop. Stunning sea views to the Golden Cap. Sign posted no camping but not enforced and there is loads of room. Can get windy as quote exposed. Quiet and feels like you're miles away from anywhere. Walk back up the hill from the pub is about 30 minutes. Free between 8pm and 8am. 50p per hour otherwise.

name: Holmbush Car Park, Lyme Regis
description: £2 for 24 hours. Large long stay car park in the in city centre. Dedicated spaces for motorhomes. Close to the beach.

name: White Cross
description: Great spot, nice and quiet. Access roads are a bit narrow. Outstanding views. Lots of walks nearby and you're right in the middle of nature.

name: Estuary View
description: Beautiful views, plenty of space. Frequently used by dog walkers. Sometimes gets a bit busy but quiet at night.

name: Darts Farm
description: Parking next to farm shop and outdoor shop.  Playgound,  lamas, cows, maize maze and more including bird watching area in the wetlands nearby. Great stop for one night. Outdoor water taps and toilets are in the cafe when its open.

name: Teignmouth Lower Point
description: Free over night but pay and display during the day. Stunning place to wake up, close to local amenities.

name: SW Coast Path - NT Car Park
description: Tarmac and gravel National Trust Car Park. Honesty box for donations. No access restrictions on the car park but narrow lanes to get there. Car park is nice and sheltered.

name: Lime Coffee Company
description: Car park close to Lime Coffee Company. Public toilets nearby. Seconds from the beach.

name: Slapton Sands Memorial
description: Car park for the Slapton Sands Monument. Right on the beach. Stunning location. £5 for overnight parking.

name: Torcross
description: Torcross Car Park. Right next to beach and nature reserve. Close to pug and local shops.

name: Gwaun Hepste - Four Falls Trail
description: Car park for one of the waterfall walks. Can get busy in good weather and during the summer.

name: Dryslwyn Castle
description: Next to the ruined Dryslwyn Castle, on the banks of the River Towy is this gorgeous picnic area nestled under deciduous trees. Entrance to the castle is free. Very peaceful spot but no services.

name: Porthkerry Country Park
description: Lovely and peaceful car park in the Porthkerry Country Park. Next to Marcos in the Park cafe, which has toilets and is open for breakfast. 5 minutes walk to the beach and there are loads of walks in the woodlands in the Country Park.  No tent camping but overnight parking is fine.

name: Foel Eryr
description: Car park in the Preseli Hills, stunning views. Occasional traffic and is exposed so can get windy!

name: Banks of the River Elan
description: Parking off the side of the road on the Banks of the River Elan. Picnic bench is located at the co-ords. Toilets and visitor center are close by. Easy access to loads of walks.

name: Caban Coch Dam
description: Parking area for the Caban Coch Dam. Popular parking spot but okay for a night or two. Absolutely stunning location, with great access to local walks. Short walk to the visitor center.

name: Field near Sennen
description: Not always open, but a nice meadow where you can overnight.

name: Riverside Spot
description: Nice spot next to a river.

name: Rhayader Environmental Services
description: Free car park a short walk from the center of Rhayader. Quiet and sheltered. Quiet but sometimes lights are on in the Environmental Services center.

name: Llyn Clywedog, Afon Biga
description: Severn Trent Water car park on the bank of the Afon Biga. Incredibly quiet location. No amenities.

name: Clywedog Reservoir
description: Incredible elevated views over Clywedog Reservoir. Car park is set back from the road and fairly spacious. There are picnic benches and bins but no other services. Quiet at night.

name: Ceri Ridgeway
description: Forest car park right on the border between England and Wales. Access road is unpaved.

name: Clun
description: Small car park next to pubic toilets in the center of Clun. Right on the banks of the River Clun and next to a historic bridge and castle. Its definitely worth the short walk up the hill to investigate the castle. Close to local pubs and amenities.

name: Sugar Loaf
description: National Trust car park for Sugar Loaf. Fairly level hard standing. Stunning views over the valley and Gilwern. Perfect starting point for walks over the Sugar Loaf so gets busy during the day. Gets quiet at night though. Access is steep.

name: Mortimer Forest - Vinnalls
description: Car park is height restricted to about 2.2m. Great access to loads of walks and mountain biking. There are some spaces before the height barrier.

name: Llangynidr
description: Large tarmac car park in Llangynidr. Quiet at night and close to local amenities.

name: Ludlow View Lay-by
description: Lay-by on Whitcliffe Road with views over Ludlow. Okay for one night but wouldn't want to stay longer than that.

name: Lay-by outside Mamble
description: Lay-by set back from the road outside Mamble off the A465. Well sheltered spot, trees eliminate some of the road noise but not all of it. Good for a stop over on route.

name: North of Craven Arms
description: Small car park north of Newinton. Good access to Shropshire Hills AONB. Quite close to railway so occasionally noisy.

name: Small Batch Carvan and Camping
description: Friendly campsite in Little Stretton at the foot of the Long Mynd. £16 per night. Stunning setting.

name: Carding Mill Valley
description: Overnight camping not allowed here. Lots of local campsites though.

name: Mortimer Forest - Black Pool
description: Car park in Mortimers Forest. Great for mountain biking and forest walks. Good signal. Access is signposted "Forest Walks"

name: Castle Hill - Far Side
description:
Nestled on the Northern edge of the Shropshire Hills Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty, this wild spot gives expansive views over some stunning terrain.
No facilities as the spot is definitely in the wilderness.

name: Brow Farm Campsite
description: Located in Ratlinghope to the west of the Long Mynd. £7 per person per night. Stunning setting and close to local pubs and shops. Campsite is fully equipped. Easy Access to walks and mountain biking.

name: Stiperstones National Nature Reserve
description: Stiperstones National Nature Reserve - Knolls Car Park. Not as level as it could be for sleeping but this spot provides stunning views and easy access to walks including the Devil's Chair summit.

name: The Bog Mine
description: Close to The Bog Visitor Centre. Stunning scenery. Short walk to Devil's Chair. In summer there are tours of the old mines.

name: Nipstone Campsite
description: In the bog this campsite gives access to multiple stunning walks and rides.

name: Snailbeach Village Hall
description: Public car park close to the mines. Short walk to great local pub.

name: Welshpool Cattle Market
description: Small car park opposite the Welshpool Livestock Sales market. Small quiet area with level parking but no facilities.

name: Bur Way
description: Overnight parking is not allowed here and the National Trust Rangers are vigilant. Views are stunning so worth a trip but stay and one of the many local camp sites.

name: Fox Hunter Memorial
description: Car park for the Fox Hunter Memorial. Decent size. On the top of hill with great views. Very exposed so can be windy.

name: Pen-Ffordd-Goch Pond
description: Car park next to Keeper's Pond. Great place to base a walk around Blorenge, lots of other walks are possible. Great views. Spot is popular with walkers so can get busy during the day.

name: The Racehorse Inn
description: Owner is happy to let you stay as long as you eat the restaurant. Great food and good beer.

name: Rhiangoll Lay-by
description: Lay-by set back off the A479 just north of Cwmdu. Rhiangoll stream is nearby.

name: Llanthony Abbey
description: Car park for the ruined Llanthony Abbey. Really peaceful spot and great to explore the Abbey.

name: Gospel Pass
description: Car Park in the middle of nowhere. Stunning views. Access can be narrow.

name: Hay Bluff / Standing Stones
description: Car park on Offa's Dyke for Hay Bluff and the Standing Stones. Quite high up so there are stunning views but its also exposed so can get windy.

name: Flat Grass Area on Offa's Dyke
description: Large flat grass area. Commonly used. Great views. Can get windy.

name: Near Grizdale
description: Nice little spot for maybe two vehicles, relatively flat, near the road but not a very busy road

name: Kenfig Nature Reserve
description: Signposted "No overnight parking" Fine during the day.

name: Nash Point
description: £10 for the night. Arrive before 1730 to get a key from the people in the cafe. Stunning

name: nr Norton Hall Farm
description: Byway frequently used for green laning at night. Not recommended.

name: Candleston Castle
description: Decent size parking areas next to the castle. Looks to be a good spot.

name: Dunraven Bay
description: Parking right on the beach. No restrictions. Sometimes gets busy.

name: Shrine of Our Lady of Penrhys
description: Car park for the Shrine to Our lady of Penrhys. At the top of the hill and easy access to local walking. Can get busy with dog walkers but peaceful at night. Great view down the valley.

name: Dare Valley Country Park
description: £20 for the night including hook up. If you call and pay in advance you can get a code to the gate to arrive late. Mostly hard standing spots. About half and hour from Bike Park Wales

name: The View Camping
description: Close to BPW, £15 per night. Rudimentary but adequate.

name: Bryn Bach Country Park
description: £20 for the night with hook up. Right on the lake shore. Great for walking and short distance to Bike Park Wales. Call ahead if likely to arrive after 5pm.

name: Caerleon Amphitheatre
description: Local "Boy Racers" can be a nuisance. Not recommended.

name: Black Rock Picnic Site
description: Stunning views of the two Severn bridges. Sometimes locals drive by late a night.

name: Eagle's Nest
description: Natural car park with stunning surroundings. Great walk up to the Eagles Nest itself opposite. No restrictions and plenty of room.

name: Lower Wyndcliff
description: Fairly flat car park off the side of the A466. Surrounded by trees. No restrictions. Great starting point for loads of walks

name: Tintern Abbey
description:
Large flat parking for Tintern Abbey on the River Wye
£3 parking but you can get a refund if you eat at The Anchor Inn.

name: Anghidi River
description: Small car park on the Anghidi stream next to the Tintern Abbey Furnace. Peaceful location that doesn't seem to be regularly visited.

name: Broadstone Park Camping and Fishery
description: A large farm with loads of space and some friendly animals. £16 per night. Loads of walks in local woods, great for exploring.

name: Speech House Woods
description: Large carpark that feels deep in the woods, well back from the road. Busy during the day with dog walkers. Close to mountain biking trails.

name: Breinton Springs
description: National Trust car park. Lots of space and no restrictions.

name: Hereford Rowing Club
description: Camping for £6 per person. Toilets and showers shared with club members. Short walk into town.

name: Afon Mellte
description: Small car park that's the get on for the Mellte. Get out is at the Dinas Rock Car Park. Quiet and close to a service station. Gets busy when the levels are good. Great access to waterfall walks.

name: Dinas Rock
description: Large car park that is the get-out for the Mellte and access to Dinas Rock. Lots of walks and loads of climbing.

name: Llyn y Fan Fach
description: Car park for the walk up Llyn y Fach. Next to the Afon Sawdde. A long way away from everything, right in the middle of the mountains. Incredibly peaceful.

name: Heol Ddu
description: Small remote car park on the south western end of the Brecon Beacons. Incredibly quiet and peaceful at night.

name: Nant Oesglyn
description: Small level gravel car park with stunning views of the North Western Brecon Beacons.

name: Mountain Road II
description: Lots of car parks along this road that have stunning views and are great for overnight stops.

name: Mountain Road III
description: Lots of car parks along this road that have stunning views and are great for overnight stops.

name: Mountain Road IV
description: Lots of car parks along this road that have stunning views and are great for overnight stops.

name: Mountain Road V
description: Lots of car parks along this road that have stunning views and are great for overnight stops.

name: Moutain Road VI
description: Lots of car parks along this road that have stunning views and are great for overnight stops.

name: Ogmore Crag
description: Parking for tidal crag at Ogmore. Okay but not ideal of overnight. The Barn is a cafe and jazz venue. Parking is surrounded by concrete pillars but there are no signposted restrictions.

name: Saint Govan's Chapel
description: Car park for Saint Govan's Chapel and Huntsman's Leap. Nice and out of the way with stunning views. Occasionally gets busy with tours. Quiet at night...unless military firing is going on.

name: West Hook Farm
description: Stunning campsite situated past Marloes in walking distance of Skoma. Stunning views to the north over all of St Brides Bay. £10 for one person, £15 for two. Great facilities.

name: St David's Bunk Barns
description: Campsite and bunk house. Rob no longer advertises camping but he's always more than happy to cater. Price is normally about £10. Great access to climbing, surfing and coastal kayaking. Short easy walk on the coastal path into St Davids itself.

name: Menai Strait View
description: Single spot next to a bench with views over the Menai Strait.

name: Y Foryd
description: Quiet spot with views over the Menai Strait to Anglesey. There are picnic benches but not other facilities. No restrictions.

name: Aberglaslyn
description: Get in for paddling the river. Sometimes busy.

name: Ty Calch
description: Stunning overnight spot with sea views over the Menai Strait to Anglesey. Views inland all the way to Snowdonia. No restrictions.

name: Ty Calch Boat Ramp
description: Parking for the boat launch. Sometimes busy during the day but quiet at night. Right on the coast.

name: Caernarfon Park and Skatepark
description: Parking with view of Caernarfor Castle. Beach is at the end of the road. Park and skate park are great fun. Bridge closes as 2300. Short walk into town.

name: Lligwy Bay
description: £10 per night, pay at the cafe. Stunning beach. Showers and toilets open during the day.

name: Llanddona Beach
description: Parking for Llanddona Beach, next to a cafe. Not suitable for large vans due to steep and narrow access.

name: Traeth Llanddona
description: Parking on the beach. Not suitable for large vans as its quite a small spot. Can get busy during the day.

name: Benllech
description: Free parking in the centre of Benllech. Right in the centre and no restrictions.

name: Sychnant Pass I
description: Great over night. Several parking spots along this road. All are popular with dog walkers but quiet at night. Mostly level but not entirely. Stunning views over the area and to Conwy Castle. Lots of walks.

name: Sychnant Pass II
description: Great over night. Several parking spots along this road. All are popular with dog walkers but quiet at night. Mostly level but not entirely. Stunning views over the area and to Conwy Castle. Lots of walks.

name: Sychnant Pass III
description: Great over night. Several parking spots along this road. All are popular with dog walkers but quiet at night. Mostly level but not entirely. Stunning views over the area and to Conwy Castle. Lots of walks.

name: Llyn Geirionydd
description: Car Park next to Llyn Geirionydd. Great for wild swimming. Toilets are open in the summer. Signposted no overnight parking but wardens are okay as long as your considerate and only staying for a night or two. Access could be difficult in larger vehicles.

name: Llanrwst Road
description: Large lay by set back from the road with plenty of space. Well shaded. Can be noisy during the day but quiet at night. Good mobile signal. Fine for one night.

name: The Holland Arms
description: Car park for The Holland Arms. Owner is happy for people to stay. Nice and quiet.

name: Trevor Quarry
description: Small, mostly level lay by on Panorama Walk in Llangollen. Nice and quiet with great views.

name: Dee Valley View
description: Really quiet spot in the wildeness north of the River Dee. Fairly flat grass area to park on.

name: Horseshoe Pass Viewpoint
description: Lay by on the side of the A452. Stunning views. Fairly level and fairly quiet a night.

name: Colemere
description: Great spot next to the lake. Great for wild swimming. Lots of dog walkers during the day but startlingly quiet at night.

name: Whittington Castle
description: Whittington Castle car park. Great for overnight. Car park is away from the road and next to the village pond and ruined castle. Very quiet at night. Pub and cafe in village. £1 for 24 hours.

name: Montford Bridge Cafe
description: Service station okay for a stop over just outside Shrewsbury on the A5. Some noise from the road.

name: Heights Tarn
description: Small lay by in the the woods. Fine for one night.

name: Machell's Coppice
description: Medium car park in Grizedale next to Coniston Water. Lake view and streams, nice and quiet. Surprisingly good signal.

name: Coniston Water - West
description: Small lay by on the lakes edge. Not private. Fine for one night lay over.

name: Arnside Knott
description: National Trust car park with no restrictions. Access is narrow. Deep in the woods.

name: Arnside Promenade
description: Parking spots overlooking the sea. Pub at the end of the road. No restrictions.

name: The Ship Inn, Sandside
description: Large car park for the The Ship Inn. Owner is happy for overnight parking. Worth calling ahead to double check.

name: Force Lane
description: Underneath the A590. Surprisingly quiet, secluded spot at the very end of Force Lane.

name: Underbarrow Road
description: Fairly sheltered, flat hard standing. Quiet and secluded. Popular with dog walkers. Donation box at the entrance.

name: Walna Scar
description: Stunning parking spot at the base of the Old Man of Coniston. Access is narrow and steep. Quiet at night.

name: Yew Tree Tarn
description: Lay by next to the tarn, great for wild swimming. Road is infrequently trafficked so quiet at night.

name: Rothay View
description: Medium car park deep in the woods near Grasmere. Some road noise from the main road below.

name: The Struggle
description: Small tarmac area off the struggle. Nice and level, unlike the road. Lots of traffic in the day but quiet at night. Stunning views.

name: Red Pit
description: National Trust car park for the Red Pit. Busy during the day but quiet at night. Stunning Views.

name: Wast Water - North West Side
description: Loads of parking spots on the North Western Side of Wast Water. All seem to be okay for overnight stops. Great starting point for walks.

name: Drigg Dunes
description: Parking in the dunes super close to the beach.

name: Seascale
description: Car park in the center of Seascale Village. Seems to be fine for overnight.

name: Bowness Knott
description: Small car park on Ennerdale Water. Long way from any busy roads.

name: Moss Force Waterfall
description: Parking for Moss Force Waterfall as well as Robinson and Grasmoor Summits. At the top of the pass, stunning views.

name: Cummock Water
description: Quiet car park on Cummock Water. Swimming is awesome. Can get busy in good weather.

name: Access to Rannerdale
description: Several car parks on this stretch of the B5289. All seems to be good for overnight and super close to the lake for a refreshing morning swim.

name: River Derwent nr Grange Bridge
description: Small gravel spots off the side of the road. Great stop-over's for a night.

name: B5289 Sheltered Crag
description: Small parking area next to what looks like a disused quarry spot. Incredibly well sheltered and quite private. Stunning views over Derwent Water.

name: Grizedale Pike Path
description: Large layby from the old mines. Stunning views over Newlands Valley. Popular parking during the day but quiet at night.

name: Noble Knott
description: Forestry Commission car park in the woods opposite the semi-permanent ice-cream truck. Great for an overnight stop.

name: Grainsgill Beck
description: Super secluded spot at the top of the River Caldew. Access is challenging as the last 100m are entirely unpaved.

name: Carrock Beck
description: Loads of various flat spots to park around this area. Access is narrow.

name: Trout Beck
description: Great if you can get access but road was blocked by boulders.

name: B5300 Coastal Spot
description: Car park right on the coast with no restrictions.

name: Solway North Plain
description: Just off the road a great grassy lay by. Surrounded by gorse with great views.

name: North of Caldbeck
description: Medium level gravel car park. Highway Agency use the area for storing gravel. Can be okay, good enough for an overnight.

name: The Holford Arms
description:
Incredibly friendly pub. Make sure you try their own, home made, home grown cider, and chilli sauce. And the waigu burger! 
Staff and owner all seemed genuinely happy to have each and every customer there. 
Campsite with hook up available out back. £10 per person without hookup. Facilities were good.

name: Stithians Reservoir
description: Near the dam, plenty of space for vehicles but no amenities.

name: Mousehole Parking
description: In the center of the small village, close to pubs and other facilities. £15 for overnight parking.

name: Cliff Road north of Mousehole
description: Roadside parking north of Mousehole

name: Drift Reservoir
description: One night stays are okay, longer stays might attract unwanted attention. Quiet car park normally used for fishing the reservoir. Dogs are not allowed around the reservoir

name: A394 Lay-by
description: Views of the sea and St Michaels Mount. Some occasional traffic noice

name: Praa Sands
description: Parking next to a beautiful lifeguarded beach. Very popular during the summer. £8 for each 24 hours. Stunning views Close to a pub with good food and there is a local surf hire shop. Car park is frequently check so ensure ticket is displayed.

name: Clifftop Carpark
description: Car park on the SW Coastal Path. Stunning views.

name: SW Coastal Path Car Park
description: Car park on top off the cliffs on the SW coastal path. Great for overnight. No amenities. Stunning Views

name: Lighthouse Hill - Portreath
description: Car park on the cliff edge. Just off the walking path with a beautiful beach below. Quiet and scenic and amazing views. Often popular with other campers but the road is quiet.

name: Beacon Drive - St Agnes
description: Quiet car park with no amenities.

name: St Anges Head
description: Couple of car parks at St Agnes Head. Great views, normally quiet at night but can get busy.

name: Londis Car Park
description: £10 for overnight. No amenities but walking distance to a Co-op and close to the town centre. Walking distance to the beach. Car park is often quiet although no views.

name: Magor Farm Campsite
description: Great campsite close to Portreath.

name: Trevella Park
description: Peaceful campsite with grass pitches or hardstanding. All the amenities and pet friendly. Around £20 per night. Close to pub.

name: Travellers Rest Pub
description:
Lovely pub with view from the car park over Mawgan Porth bay. Worth calling ahead if possible to confirm that you would like to stay overnight.
No services but welcomes motorhomes. Free to stay when a patron of the pub. Max stay 24 hours.

name: Pentire Steps Beach Car Park
description: National trust car park but not pay and display. There is a donation box. Quiet and tranquil spot.

name: St Minver Cemetery
description: Large level area on the side of a quiet lane. Nice easy overnight stop. Wouldn't stay for more than one night.

name: Trevose Head Wild Spot
description: Parking on the side of the road. Often used by locals and surfers during the day but quieter at night. Short walk to beaches. Further down the road are paid spots. Overnight camping is allowed but no amenities.

name: Northcott Mouth Car Park
description:
National Trust car park with a donation box (£2). Stunning location above Northcott Mouth Beach. Short walk into Bude (30 mins). Make sure you pop into Margaret's for a proper authentic Cornish cream tea.
No amenities so you'll need to take everything you bring.

name: Three Cliffs Bay Holiday Park
description: Fantastic Campsite with great facilities and views. You pay for the location starting at £35 a night.

name: Manorbier Beach
description: Car Park underneath Manorbier Castle. Toilets open 24/7. Signs say no overnight parking but no issues reported. Close to local amenities, beach and castle.  £5 parking for all day.

name: Carnedd Llewelyn Parking
description: Carpark for the Carnedd Llewelyn. Really in the middle of nowhere. Secluded and no facilities.

name: Watersinks CP, Malham Tarn
description: Large, flat, hard-standing car park on exposed moor near the tarn. Great walk south to Malham Cove, 'The Pavement' and Malham village with pubs.

name: Caernarfon castle view
description: Perfect for a chilled night by the water. There's usually other campers there even out of season. I love it for a cook by the sea and then a walk over the footbridge to The Anglesey for a whiskey. Note - footbridge closes at 11pm so make sure to be back van side or it's a loooong walk home!

name: Burford Parking
description: Free spot at car park. Easy acces, mostly level. Quiet, at the edge of town, easy walk to town center. Sign says max 12 hours, no further restrictions. Small river on one site. Public toilets at entrance. 50+ spaces

name: Layby near Trefin
description: Small layby fit for 3 cars, flat enough, public toilet up the hill in the village

name: Afon Glaslyn
description: Layby off the A498 next to the Glaslyn. Sometimes traffic can be a bit noisy.

name: Llyn Dinas
description: Several laybys on the A498 next to Llyn Dinas. Great if you like early morning swims!

name: Llyn Gwynant
description: Several small laybys off the A498 next to the lake. Can get busy to best to arrive late and leave early.

name: Nant Gwynant
description: Roadside parking just down from the cafe. Great for a single night. Caffi Gwynant is amazing. Easy access to the Watkin Path for Snowdon.

name: Llanberis Lagoons
description: Relaxed car park north of Llanberis. Starting point for adventure walk to abandoned ammo bunker. Public toilets at the entry to the car park.

name: Minwear Wood nr Oakwood
description: Quiet parking spot in the woods behind Oakwood and Bluestone. Access road is narrow but quiet and secluded.

name: Minwear Wood Layby
description: Layby in Minwear wood with several picnic benches, Minwear wood is behind Oakwood and Bluestone. Easy access and lots of space. Quiet and quite secluded.

name: Whitesands Bay
description:
£5 between 9am and 5pm. Free overnight. Although signposted "no overnight camping" it's normally fine during the off season. They're likely to be stricter during peak season due to the popularity of the bay. Car park is gently sloping but there are a few flat spots.

Toilets cost 40p a go (but it's easy to be sneaky and avoid it). Cafe has wifi but tends to shut quite early.

Surf is great, especially at medium to high tide. Loads of climbing around St Davids Head too.

name: Newgale Beach - 2
description: Second carpark on Newgale Beach. Comes well recommended!

name: Pebbles Cafe Car Park
description: Car park on Newgale Beach next to Pebbles Cafe. Fine for an overnight kip.

name: Maidenhall - National Trust Car Park
description: Brilliant cliff top car park with stunning sunset views.

name: Roch Gate - West
description: Layby on the westerly side of Roch Gate. Great for a quiet overnight stop on you way to the coast.

name: Roch Gate - South East
description: Layby on the south-easterly side of Roch Gate. Great for a quiet overnight stop on you way to the coast.

name: South of Wolf's Castle - Layby
description: Layby just South of Wolf's Castle on the A40.

name: Caerfachell lay by
description: quietly by in the middle of nowhere, the A-road is pretty quiet most of the time too

name: Croesgoch Layby
description: Layby just sound of Croesgoch. Gravelly and mostly flat. Road is pretty quiet

name: A40 Layby
description: Layby off the A40. Sometimes busy during the summer, but normally quiet. Some road noise as its quite close to the road.

name: Oxford
description: Small little car park overlooking a lovely big park. Paid but it is cheap. Close to shops to restock at. Less than a mile to the centre of Oxford. Peaceful overnight sleeping.
